sbs-braille-tables NEWS -- history of user-visible changes.  	-*- org -*-

* Noteworthy changes in release 1.15 (2023-??-??)
- Move all detailed accents that are not Swiss to the reduced ones
  i.e. characters like ø, ã or ÿ are now plain old reduced accents.
  This fixes part of http://redmine.sbszh.ch/issues/1745
- Fix missing dot 6 before single letter in front of apstrophe such as
  "F'".
- Translate non-breaking space as a special braille pattern, so it can
  get special treatment in sbsform.

* Noteworthy changes in release 1.14 (2021-03-22)
** Drop gnulib
- Wasn't really needed, we can manually change the version string
** Upgrade to liblouis 3.17
- Migrate ~nocross~ to ~nocross always~
- make use of the extended ~nocross~ possibilities
- add test cases for the rules that have been upgraded to work with
  ~nocross~

* Noteworthy changes in release 1.13 (2020-09-23)
- Upgrade to modern liblouis, i.e. use 'nocross always' instead of
  just 'nocross'.

* Noteworthy changes in release 1.12.5 (2019-09-06)
- Revert the Always convert Esszet (ß) to lowercase change as it seems
  to break dictionary based translation.

* Noteworthy changes in release 1.12.4 (2019-09-03)
- Add corrects for left-pointing angle quotation marks before hyphen.
- Always convert Esszet (ß) to lowercase.
- Fix `make distcheck`.

* Noteworthy changes in release 1.12.3 (2019-09-02)
- Add a correct for hyphen after square bracket

* Noteworthy changes in release 1.12.2 (2019-09-02)
- Fix some problems with hyphen

* Noteworthy changes in release 1.12.1 (2019-08-20)
- Add a noletsign for Esszet (ß)

* Noteworthy changes in release 1.12.0 (2019-03-22)
- Fix a problem with Wortersatzstrich initial
- Fix a problem with Minuszeichen nach ( [ › »
- Fix translation of 'n' als Wort (zwischen Blanks)
- Add YAML tests

* Noteworthy changes in release 1.2 (2011-02-14)
    - Improve tables

* Noteworthy changes in release 1.1 (2010-07-14) [beta]
    - Add git-version-gen
    - Add do-release-commit-and-tag

* Noteworthy changes in release 1.0.9
    - Update whitelists

* Noteworthy changes in release 1.0.8
    - Whitespace handling fixes
    - Lautgruppen nach Apo
    - Dummy-Zahlen
    - Korrektur "ver"
    
* Noteworthy changes in release 1.0.7
    - Fix error in whitespace handling

* Noteworthy changes in release 1.0.6
    - Fix g1 white list

* Noteworthy changes in release 1.0.5
    - minor white list corrections due to faulty automatic generation

* Noteworthy changes in release 1.0.4
    - Fix a bug with abbrevs

* Noteworthy changes in release 1.0.3
    - white list improvements
    - hyphenation improvements
    - minor corrections

* Noteworthy changes in release 1.0.2
  Added a version table which allows to query the version of the installed tables


